.SH "NAME"
.sp
yabai
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fByabai\fP [\fB\-v\fP,\fB\-\-version\fP|\fB\-V\fP,\fB\-\-verbose\fP|\fB\-m\fP,\fB\-\-message\fP \fImsg\fP|\fB\-c\fP,\fB\-\-config\fP \fIconfig_file\fP|\fB\-\-install\-sa\fP|\fB\-\-uninstall\-sa\fP|\fB\-\-load\-sa\fP]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
\fByabai\fP is a tiling window manager for macOS based on binary space partitioning.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.sp
\fB\-v\fP, \fB\-\-version\fP
.RS 4
Print the version and exit.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-V\fP, \fB\-\-verbose\fP
.RS 4
Output debug information to stdout.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-m\fP, \fB\-\-message\fP \fI<msg>\fP
.RS 4
Send message to a running instance of yabai.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-c\fP, \fB\-\-config\fP \fI<config_file>\fP
.RS 4
Use the specified configuration file.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-install\-sa\fP
.RS 4
Install the scripting\-addition into /System/Library/ScriptingAdditions. Must be ran as root.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-uninstall\-sa\fP
.RS 4
Remove the scripting\-addition from /System/Library/ScriptingAdditions. Must be ran as root.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-load\-sa\fP
.RS 4
Loads the scripting\-addition into Dock.app.
.RE
.SH "DEFINITIONS"
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
DIR_SEL     := north | east | south | west

WINDOW_SEL  := prev | next | last | DIR_SEL

DISPLAY_SEL := prev | next | last | arrangement index (1\-based)

SPACE_SEL   := prev | next | last | mission\-control index (1\-based)
.fi
.if n .RE
.SH "DOMAINS"
.SS "Config"
.SS "General Syntax"
.sp
yabai \-m config [\-\-space \fI<mission\-control index>\fP] <setting> [<value>]
.RS 4
Get or set the value of <setting>.
.RE
.SS "Global Settings"
.sp
Colors are in the form \fI#AARRGGBB\fP, booleans are \fIon\fP or \fIoff\fP.
.sp
\fImouse_follows_focus\fP
.RS 4
When focusing a window, put the mouse at its center.
.RE
.sp
\fIfocus_follows_mouse\fP
.RS 4
Focus the window under the mouse. Accept the following values: \fBautofocus\fP, \fBautoraise\fP, \fBoff\fP.
.RE
.sp
\fIwindow_shadow\fP
.RS 4
Draw shadow for windows. Accept the following values: \fBon\fP, \fBfloat\fP, \fBoff\fP.
.RE
.sp
\fIwindow_border\fP
.RS 4
Draw border for windows.
.RE
.sp
\fIwindow_border_width\fP
.RS 4
Width of window borders.
.RE
.sp
\fIactive_window_border_color\fP
.RS 4
Color of the border of the focused window.
.RE
.sp
\fInormal_window_border_color\fP
.RS 4
Color of the border of an unfocused window.
.RE
.sp
\fIinsert_window_border_color\fP
.RS 4
Color of the \fBwindow \-\-insert\fP message selection.
.RE
.sp
\fIactive_window_opacity\fP
.RS 4
Opacity of the focused window.
.RE
.sp
\fInormal_window_opacity\fP
.RS 4
Opacity of an unfocused window.
.RE
.sp
\fIsplit_ratio\fP
.RS 4
Default split ratio.
.RE
.sp
\fIauto_balance\fP
.RS 4
Balance the window tree upon change, so that all windows occupy the same area.
.RE
.sp
\fImouse_modifier\fP
.RS 4
Keyboard modifier used for moving and resizing windows. Accept the following values: \fBcmd\fP, \fBalt\fP, \fBshift\fP, \fBctrl\fP, \fBfn\fP.
.RE
.sp
\fImouse_action1\fP, \fImouse_action2\fP
.RS 4
Action performed when pressing \fImouse_modifier\fP + \fIbutton<n>\fP. Accept the following values: \fBmove\fP, \fBresize\fP.
.RE
.SS "Space Settings"
.sp
\fIlayout\fP
.RS 4
Set the layout of the selected space. Accept the following values: \fBbsp\fP, \fBfloat\fP.
.RE
.sp
\fItop_padding\fP, \fIbottom_padding\fP, \fIleft_padding\fP, \fIright_padding\fP
.RS 4
Padding added at the sides of the selected space.
.RE
.sp
\fIwindow_gap\fP
.RS 4
Size of the gap that separates windows for the selected space.
.RE
.SS "Display"
.SS "General Syntax"
.sp
yabai \-m display \fICOMMAND\fP
.SS "COMMAND"
.sp
\fB\-\-focus\fP \fIDISPLAY_SEL\fP
.RS 4
Focus the given display.
.RE
.SS "Space"
.SS "General Syntax"
.sp
yabai \-m space \fICOMMAND\fP
.SS "COMMAND"
.sp
\fB\-\-focus\fP \fISPACE_SEL\fP
.RS 4
Focus the given space.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-move\fP \fIDISPLAY_SEL\fP
.RS 4
Move the active space to the given display.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-create\fP
.RS 4
Create a new space on the active display.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-destroy\fP
.RS 4
Remove the currently active space.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-balance\fP
.RS 4
Adjust the split ratios of the active space so that all windows occupy the same area.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-mirror\fP \fIx\-axis|y\-axis\fP
.RS 4
Flip the tree of the active space.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-rotate\fP \fI90|180|270\fP
.RS 4
Rotate the tree of the active space.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-padding\fP \fI<top>:<bottom>:<left>:<right>\fP
.RS 4
Padding added at the sides of the space.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-gap\fP \fI<gap>\fP
.RS 4
Size of the gap that separates windows.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-toggle\fP \fIpadding|gap\fP
.RS 4
Toggle space setting on or off.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-layout\fP \fIbsp|float\fP
.RS 4
Set the layout of the space.
.RE
.SS "Window"
.SS "General Syntax"
.sp
yabai \-m window \fICOMMAND\fP
.SS "COMMAND"
.sp
\fB\-\-focus\fP \fIWINDOW_SEL\fP
.RS 4
Focus the window in the given direction.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-swap\fP \fIWINDOW_SEL\fP
.RS 4
Swap position with the window in the given direction.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-warp\fP \fIWINDOW_SEL\fP
.RS 4
Re\-insert, splitting the window in the given direction.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-insert\fP \fIDIR_SEL\fP
.RS 4
Select the splitting area of the focused window. If the current selection matches \fIDIR_SEL\fP, the action will be undone.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-grid\fP \fI<rows>:<cols>:<start\-x>:<start\-y>:<width>:<height>\fP
.RS 4
Set the window frame based on a self\-defined grid.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-move\fP \fI<dx>:<dy>\fP
.RS 4
Move window by \fIdx\fP pixels horizontally and \fIdy\fP pixels vertically.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-resize\fP \fItop|left|bottom|right|top_left|top_right|bottom_right|bottom_left:<dx>:<dy>\fP
.RS 4
Resize window by moving the given handle \fIdx\fP pixels horizontally and \fIdy\fP pixels vertically.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-toggle\fP \fIfloat|sticky|split|border|fullscreen|native\-fullscreen\fP
.RS 4
Toggle the selected property of a window.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-display\fP \fIDISPLAY_SEL\fP
.RS 4
Send the window to the given display.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-space\fP \fISPACE_SEL\fP
.RS 4
Send the window to the given space.
.RE
.SS "Query"
.SS "General Syntax"
.sp
yabai \-m query \fICOMMAND\fP [\fIARGUMENT\fP]
.SS "COMMAND"
.sp
\fB\-\-displays\fP
.RS 4
Retrieve information about displays.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-spaces\fP
.RS 4
Retrieve information about spaces.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-windows\fP
.RS 4
Retrieve information about windows.
.RE
.SS "ARGUMENT"
.sp
\fB\-\-display\fP [\fI<arrangement index\fP]
.RS 4
Constrain matches to the selected display.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-space\fP [\fI<mission\-control index>\fP]
.RS 4
Constrain matches to the selected space.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-window\fP
.RS 4
Constrain matches to the focused window.
.RE
.SH "EXIT CODES"
.sp
If \fByabai\fP can\(cqt handle a message, it will return a non\-zero exit code.
